<TEXT>
a symbolic arab force being created to help 
protect saudi arabia from its hostile neighbor iraq pales beside 
the massive fighting machine the united states is sending 
the contributions of egypt syria and morocco will be relatively 
small at best and it is hard to pin down just what those countries 
are sending 
the main significance of the force appears to be that it enables 
the saudis to justify the american presence by telling arabs leery 
of foreigners that brother arabs have also come to their rescue 
president hosni mubarak of egypt architect of the arab league 
resolution that brought about the arab commitment says syria and 
morocco will join egypt in sending troops moslem but nonarab 
pakistan and bangladesh say they will also send troops 
the force will be a few thousand at most insignificant as a 
military threat to 160000 iraqis massed with tanks on the saudi 
border 
we are sending not more than 2000 soldiers to help the 
saudis under the command of the saudi arabian armed forces 
mubarak told reporters at alexandria i dont compare our forces 
with the us forces 
the pentagon on washington has said the united states force 
might eventually reach 250000 if necessary 
little has been said officially about the moroccan and syrian 
forces which sources in the persian gulf area have said would 
total about 5000 men each 
official sources in rabat said morocco has dispatched 1200 
soldiers so far 
syrian officials have said nothing about the their force saudi 
diplomats reported earlier in the week that syrian soldiers had 
arrived but col andrew duncan of the londonbased international 
institute of strategic studies said he understands they amount to 
nothing more than a planeload of staff officers 
duncan added that the arab force appears to include the wrong 
kind of soldier needed to face saddam husseins strike forces 
the sort of forces coming in really arent the best things to 
use in armored warfare in the desert duncan said by telephone 
once elite paratroopers make their marvelous parachute drop they 
dont have much more they can do against tanks 
egyptian defense ministry sources have said egypt is sending 
commandos paratroops chemicalwarfare specialists and infantrymen 
the defense ministry has not said how many soldiers are going 
in a statement friday its first on the deployment the ministry 
said elements of the egyptian armed forces left the homeland 
and have arrived in the areas of operation assigned to them in 
saudi arabia 
on aug 10 mubarak pushed through an arab league summit 
conference the resolution establishing the joint force the idea 
purportedly was to help saudi arabia defend itself if iraq invades 
via kuwait which it seized on aug 2 
the resolution also gave arab approval to the saudis request 
for us help for saudi arabias usarmed 123000man military 
complaints from arabs began as soon as the invitation was 
announced feelings on the subject run so high that mubaraks 
resolution passed at the arab summit by a bare majority twelve of 
the 20 leaders attending voting yes 
six of the 12 including saudi arabia and kuwaits ousted 
government were gulf states concerned about iraqi expansion 
military analyst duncan said even a 15000man arab force would 
be still token especially if youre only talking about men they 
would need something to fight with other than rifles and machine 
guns 
