<TEXT>
1933at age 15 pearl bailey made her stage debut in an amateur 
night at the pearl theatre in philadelphia where her brother had 
already performed she sang talk of the town and poor 
butterfly and earned 5 for winning first prize 
1946appearing on broadway for the first time she played 
butterfly in the johnny mercerharold arlen allblack musical 
st louis woman and stole the show with renditions of 
legalize my name and a womans prerogative she received 
the donaldson award for best newcomer on broadway 
1950she appeared in two musicals arms and the girl and 
bless you all which ran for 84 performances 
1954after a fouryear absence she starred on broadway in the 
truman capoteharold arlen musical house of flowers with 
bailey playing madame fleur the owner of a lavish west indian 
bordello house of flowers ran for 165 performances 
1967her career peaks with her starring role in an allblack 
version of hello dolly an enormous critical and commercial 
success cab calloway was her leading man and at the annual tony 
awards she received a special award for her performance she was 
again in the title role in a 1975 revival 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
1947she made her film debut in variety girl a showcase for 
paramount performers and sang two specialty numbers 
1954appeared in otto premingers adaptation of the allblack 
broadway musical carmen jones playing frankie one of carmens 
friends 
1956appeared in the comedy that certain feeling which 
starred bob hope and eva marie saint 
1959again working with preminger she played maria the cookshop 
woman in the film version of george gershwins porgy and bess 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
recorded for several labels including coral decca and 
columbia among the albums she made were bad old days cole 
porter song book and echoes of an era 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
in 1966 along with carol channing an earlier star of hello 
dolly she costarred in the special carol channing and pearl 
bailey on broadway she also guested on specials for bob hope and 
bing crosby and appeared on talk shows hosted by milton berle 
johnny carson and perry como among others 
she had her own series the pearl bailey show which ran 
during the 197071 season 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
she wrote several books including two autobiographies raw 
pearl amd talking to myself and a cookbook called pearls 
kitchen an extraordinary cookbook 
she received the uso woman of the year award in 1969 and was 
appointed as a special advisor to the united states mission of the 
united nations general assembly in 1975 by president ford 
</TEXT>
