<TEXT>
iraqs armed takeover of 
kuwait has left five americanflagged oil tankers worth nearly 150 
million in legal limbo as to who owns them shipping industry 
sources say 
the ships are the last of 11 kuwaiti tankers reflagged by the 
united states in mid1987 to ensure american naval protection from 
attacks by iran in the persian gulf 
they remained under the stars and stripes when the other six 
reverted to kuwaiti registry following the iraniraq ceasefire on 
august 20 1988 
one of the five the chesapeake city reportedly just escaped 
seizure when the iraqi invasion on aug 2 caught it forging into 
kuwaiti waters 
the 401000ton crude carrier bridgeton the worlds sixth 
largest ship and the four oil products tankers of about 80000 
tons each were last reported at anchor at ports around the gulf 
while officials ponder their status said walter oates a us 
maritime administration spokesman 
the vessels have been manned for the past year by american 
crews about 30 per ship 
oates in a telephone interview said kuwaiti officials had 
recently indicated they wanted to deflag the other five ships 
but thats obviously a moot point now 
another us maritime source who declined to be named said the 
ships probably would remain under us jurisdiction pending 
clarification of their legal status 
he said it was a strange situation nobody really knows 
what happens next 
the kuwaitis in 1987 set up a delaware corporation chesapeake 
shipping co to meet us legal requirements that americanflagged 
ships have us owners the firm could not be reached for comment 
philip wake a senior consultant for lloyds maritime information 
services in london said that as long as delaware shipping co 
remains a legal entity kuwait probably would be considered the 
owner of the tankers 
but when something like this crops up its a political 
question to a large extent and when it gets to the lawyers they 
can have a field day he said 
wake said an ultra large crude carrier like the bridgeton is 
currently worth about 40 million on the tanker market with oil 
products tankers in the 80000ton range worth about 27 million 
