<TEXT>
a british television broadcasting 
satellite orbited earth today after a successful ride into space 
aboard an unmanned delta rocket 
the liftoff friday night was nearly two hours behind schedule 
because of thunderstorms and lastminute problems with a computer 
used to display range data 
the british satellite broadcasting satellite called marcopolo 
2 will transmit programs directly to thousands of homes in britain 
one of the nice things about this launch is that it was not 
only successful but the holds delays worked out for a night 
launch which is always more spectacular said former astronaut 
charles pete conrad now a vice president for rocket builder 
mcdonnell douglas 
the satellite separated from the booster as planned about 28 
minutes after the 842 pm liftoff from cape canaveral air force 
station an onboard kick motor is to put the satellite into a 
22300milehigh orbit on sunday 
an identical spacecraft marcopolo 1 was launched aboard a 
delta rocket last aug 27 it was the united states first 
commercial launch of a payload into orbit fridays launch was the 
ninth 
the cost of both marcopolo satellites and launches is about 300 
million said ellis griffiths director of engineering for british 
satellite broadcasting 
marcopolo 2 eventually will be situated over the atlantic ocean 
near the first satellite each 1450pound spacecraft has a 
lifetime of at least 10 years 
once marcopolo 2 becomes fully operational in early december it 
will enable the company to transmit at full power over five 
transponder channels only one channel currently is being beamed at 
full power the other four are at half power 
british satellite broadcasting is the only company in the world 
that is transmitting television programs directly from orbiting 
satellites to homes griffiths said so far there have been no 
satellite problems he said 
unlike in the united states its not always feasible to mount 
large satellite dishes in britain griffiths said in large 
blocks of tenements to have huge dishes everywhere its just 
totally impractical he said 
about 50000 units have been installed in british homes so 
signals can be received directly from the powerful satellites 
griffiths said each unit consists of a 157inchsquare antenna 
and a receiver about the size of a videocassette recorder 
british satellite broadcasting expects to have about 1 million 
units installed by the end of the year griffiths said 
