ambassadors of the five permanent members 
of the security council and their senior military aides have held 
an extraordinary joint meeting to discuss a larger un military 
role in the persian gulf crisis 
also friday the security council expressed anxiety over the 
fate of foreigners trapped in kuwait and iraq and called on the 
un secretarygeneral to take all necessary steps to help them 
the security council was scheduled to meet again today on the 
crisis which began aug 2 when iraqi tanks and troops poured into 
kuwait and then massed at the saudi arabian border 
french ambassador pierre louis blanc said the five permanent 
members of the council met friday to exchange information on the 
naval activities in the gulf and in the area he spoke to 
reporters after the meeting at the french mission 
the meeting was attended by un envoys of the united states 
britain china france and the soviet union and by military 
advisers of the five governments together known as the security 
councils military staff committee 
the committee was created 44 years ago but has been inactive 
meeting on a perfunctory basis two times a month 
diplomats said fridays meeting was not ordinary it included 
senior us british and french officers a senior soviet official 
was unable to attend and the level of the chinese military was not 
known 
no immediate indication surfaced that the five were moving to 
form a joint un military command in the gulf but western 
observers said the group moved with extraordinary speed to discuss 
coordination and a un military role 
we wont have a un army tomorrow one observer said on 
condition of anonymity but we could have exchange of information 
and coordination letting each other know about rules of 
engagement and that is quite significant 
by un standards that is whirlwind progress the observer 
said 
under the un charter the military staff committee is charged 
with coordinating all un military actions of an enforcement 
nature excluding peacekeeping 
it is intended to organize and command joint military 
operations which never have come into existence the last time the 
un flag was flown in a un enforcement operation was during the 
195053 korean war 
that war was not strictly a un operation however and was 
handed over to the united states 
