black factions fought running 
battles today with axes spears and homemade guns raising the toll 
from this weeks fighting to more than 200 dead and hundreds 
wounded 
the antiapartheid african national congress on friday accused 
the government of encouraging the violence in the black townships 
to justify repressive measures and to prolong white rule 
police fired tear gas to disperse rival bands of zulus a tribe 
that has largely rejected a future government controlled nelson 
mandelas anc and the proanc xhosas in the sprawling black 
township of soweto 
war bands burned houses and stoned vehicles witnesses said 
the countrys top police official gen johann van der merwe 
