johannesburg on sunday and spread during the week to four more 
areas including soweto southwest of johannesburg the fighting 
pits zulus of the inkatha movement against mostly xhosa supporters 
of the african national congress 
the anc accused the governments security forces friday of 
plotting to use inkatha to stir up tribal rivalry in the townships 
around johannesburg more than 5000 people have died in fighting 
between inkatha and anc supporters in the eastern natal province in 
the past five years 
the anc issued a statement saying state security forces in 
collusion with inkatha were trying to spread a climate of fear 
and terror in the towns which are known to be strongholds of the 
