an earthquake measuring 54 on the 
richter scale shook northeastern iran saturday the official 
islamic republic news agency reported 
there were no immediate reports of casualties or destruction 
said the report monitored in cyprus 
the quake was felt in two northeastern cities gorgan and 
bojnourd which are about 120 miles apart 
