caspian sea bojnourd is 211 miles northwest of the provincial 
center of mashhad in khorasan province 
scores of sharp aftershocks have rolled through iran since the 
june 21 earthquake that destroyed a large swath of northwestern 
iran killing almost 40000 people and wounded tens of thousands 
the richter scale is a gauge of energy released by an 
earthquake measured by a seismograph as ground motion an 
earthquake of magnitude 5 can cause considerable damage while one 
of 6 can cause severe damage 
the june quake in iran registered above 73 
