conceived in the 1950s 
the planes are owned by 16 airlines which also will be 
providing the crews to operate them the airlift support is 
expected to be needed for several weeks the pentagon said 
air force gen hansford t johnson commander of the us 
transportation command and military airlift command announced 
friday that he would activate the first stage of the civilian 
reserve air fleet to meet the growing airlift requirements for 
us forces 
his decision enables the callup of as many as 38 aircraft to 
carry soldiers and cargo to the persian gulf region 
stages two and three if activated could deploy as many as 300 
