president bush on saturday signed a 
bill prompted by the alaska oil spill setting tougher standards 
for ship construction and authorizing a 1 billion fund to cover 
cleanup costs and damages not paid by the spiller 
bush complained that the measure contained a highly 
objectionable moratorium on exploration for oil and natural gas 
