<TEXT>
thousands of colombians marched in the 
streets of the capital saturday to mark the anniversary of the 
assassination of a leading presidential candidate who was shot and 
killed by drug traffickers 
the slaying of luis carlos galan led to a major escalation in 
fighting between the government and the medellin drug cartel the 
fighting has claimed hundreds of lives 
president cesar gaviria who had served as galans campaign 
manager attended a morning mass saturday along with his cabinet 
and the slain candidates family 
afterwards thousands of people many in tears marched through 
downtown bogota to the central cemetery where galan is buried 
marches were planned in cities throughout colombia radio 
stations said they would stop broadcasting for one minute at 745 
pm the time galan was killed by gunmen working for drug 
traffickers 
newspapers dedicated long articles and columns to the life and 
death of the assassinated leader 
galan was shot at a political rally near bogota on aug 18 
1989 polls indicated that the charismatic 46yearold senator 
would have won a landslide victory in the presidential elections 
immediately following galans death the government of former 
president virgilio barco began a major crackdown on drug 
traffickers 
since then drug lords have killed about 500 colombians 
officials say among the dead were 200 police officers in medellin 
colombias second largest city and two other presidential 
candidates 
gaviria has said his government will continue the hardline 
stance galan advocated against drug traffickers 
following galans death the united states sent colombia 65 
million in emergency aid to fight cocaine smugglers the assistance 
included 20 helicopters bulletproof vests and communications 
equipment 
authorities have said the governments antidrug offensive has 
severely weakened the cartel 
security forces have seized some 41 tons of cocaine so far this 
year compared to 33 tons during all of 1989 us officials say 
the price of cocaine has risen dramatically and supply is down 
the government has extradited 22 suspected drug smugglers to the 
united states 
colombias medellin and cali drug cartels supply an estimated 80 
percent of the cocaine used in the united states 
