<TEXT>
saudi arabia is ready to increase 
its oil output by up to 2 million barrels a day to help offset the 
world shortfall caused by the iraqi invasion of kuwait the oil 
minister indicated saturday 
oil minister hisham nazer told a news conference in jiddah that 
his country would have no alternative but to increase oil 
production unilaterally if opec does not convene an emergency 
meeting requested by saudi arabia 
if the opec session fails to get off the ground then it will 
be left for each member state to decide alone on the increase in 
output he told the western and saudi journalists 
immediately means immediately he said when asked how long 
the saudis will wait for the organization of petroleum exporting 
countries to schedule a meeting 
he said that saudi arabia the worlds largest oil exporter 
could increase its output by up to 2 million barrels a day within 
days 
but he said saudi arabia alone cannot make up for the 4 million 
barrels of oil a day that international markets lost by the removal 
of iraqi and kuwaiti oil 
by invading and annexing kuwait iraq gained control of about 20 
percent of the worlds oil reserves and the withdrawal of its 
crude from the market has caused oil and gas prices to soar 
most nations have declared support for un sanctions against 
baghdad including an oil embargo 
nazer said venezuela and the united arab emirates each could 
increase output by 500000 barrels a day but this would leave us 
with 1 million barrels less 
in georgetown guyana venezuelan president carlos andres perez 
told reporters friday he favors convening an opec meeting soon but 
did not indicate when it might take place 
he said opec has an obligation to maintain stability in the oil 
market 
nazer said the saudis are awaiting responses to their request 
for an opec meeting he criticized some opec members such as 
nigeria which have resisted holding another meeting less than a 
month after the oil exporters last session in switzerland 
the last meeting on july 2627 in geneva came after iraq accused 
kuwait and the united arab emirates of flooding the market with oil 
and driving down prices 
at that meeting opec fixed a production ceiling of almost 225 
million barrels a day for the 13 member nations to defend a 
21abarrel price saudi arabia agreed to a production quota of 
538 million barrels a day 
nazer commented now this has all been changed the price now 
stands at 28 per barrel and the daily production figure is far 
less than 224 million the shortage of 4 million barrels a day can 
increase if the tension continues 
all opec members together should make up for this shortage 
we will not let the third world countries down and so will 
increase production 
nazer said failure to stabilize oil prices and production would 
not only devastate developing nations but also hurt opec in the 
long run 
less oil would lead to higher prices in the marketplace trigger 
a recession among industrial nations and spur them to develop 
alternative energy sources he said 
he suggested that the oil situation could improve if the united 
states and other industrialized countries open their strategic 
stockpiles to the market 
the reporters were invited by the saudi government to travel to 
the red sea city of jidday about 1000 miles from where thousands 
of us troops and other members of a multinational force are 
deploying on the persian gulf 
oil industry sources in saudi arabia told the associated press 
on friday that the kingdom would increase its output 
saudi arabia is the dominant opec state with a quarter of known 
world reserves 
the sources speaking on condition of anonymity predicted that 
the opec session called by saudi arabia would convene monday or 
tuesday in geneva 
they did not say what might happen if not all opec members 
agreed to participate 
iraq has criticized saudi arabia for calling the meeting saying 
the saudis created the shortfall by blocking iraqi oil exports from 
the transsaudi oil pipeline 
in saudi arabias first direct official comment nazer confirmed 
that his country had turned away two iraqi tankers that tried to 
load oil from the pipeline terminal he said it did so after the 
un security council resolution on sanctions 
meanwhile the turmoil in the middle east where thousands of 
us troops are being deployed to defend saudi arabia against a 
possible iraqi attack continued to create havoc on world markets 
unleaded gasoline hit a record high friday on the new york 
