pearl bailey was 15 when she sang poor 
butterfly in an amateur contest and won a 5 prize she went on 
to win the hearts of millions as a singer actress and americas 
ambassador of love 
bailey 72 died at a philadelphia hospital friday night 
she was a rare pearl her road manager eb smith said 
saturday 
bailey was known for playing matchmaker dolly in the black 
version of the musical hello dolly on broadway from 1967 to 
1969 others loved her throaty expressive versions of bill 
bailey wont you please come home st louis blues row 
row row and thats good enough for me 
but baileys favorite role was that of ambassador of love 
and special delegate to the united nations where she could spread 
