george seabrook wing an aeronautical 
engineer who invented the fastener used in nearly all aircraft and 
some spacecraft as well died tuesday at age 74 
a selftaught engineer wing invented the hishear rivet 
first used in the p51 mustang the workhorse world war ii fighter 
plane the rivet was onethird lighter than previous fasteners and 
has since been used on all types of commercial and military 
aircraft as well as nasas apollo missions to the moon 
a native of kewanee wis he worked at several aviation 
companies designing the fastener while at north american aviation 
in 1943 he left to found the company that became hishear corp in 
the los angeles suburb of torrance a maker of fasteners explosive 
separation devices boosters and rivetmaking tools 
wing died at torrance medical center after a brief battle with 
cancer 
</TEXT>
