<TEXT>
the persian gulf crisis has combined with 
alarming us economic statistics to make even some upbeat 
forecasters tilt their outlooks toward the gloomy side 
many now believe the federal reserve faces an ever more 
treacherous minefield in charting a course for us interest rates 
over the next several months 
the key worry is that evidence disclosed this past week on 
consumer prices construction and trade depict an economy leaning 
dangerously toward both recession and higher inflation even before 
the usiraq faceoff in the gulf which has sent crude oil prices 
skyward 
i think the statistics still point to slow growth and the 
