remains in the 2530 range they said oil is only one element of 
the inflation picture 
others say comparisons to previous oilprice shocks of the 70s 
are flawed and misleading because other forces were at work in 
those times such as sharply higher wages and a rapidly expanding 
money supply which were pushing inflation up relentlessly 
we used to have an economy with a lot of builtin price 
pressures spirals in all sorts of things said thomas f 
carpenter of asb capital management in washington those things 
are absent all areas are soft 
still carpenter said oils rise will permeate the economy with 
higher prices you cant get around it 
